<subSubSection id="91A7657E6B54BB77FF1DC464021CF96F" pageId="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D90236F56B54BB77FF1DC464021CF96F" blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FF1DC4640074F9DB" bold="true" box="[189,318,1554,1580]" pageId="3">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet is dedicated to Dr.Armando Jesús Urquiola Cruz (1949–2009), eminent Cuban botanist, founder of the Botanical Garden of Pinar de Río, who dedicated his life to the study and conservation of the flora of Pinar de Río, the 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FEE7C42C00F7F983" box="[327,445,1626,1652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Myrtaceae</taxonomicName>
family and Cuban aquatic plants. Professor Urquiola was the first to recognize this species as new to science, in an expedition with the first author in 2007.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91A7657E6B54BB77FF1DC4D70324F7D3" pageId="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D90236F56B54BB77FF1DC4D7023AF84F" blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FF1DC4D700ABF94C" bold="true" box="[189,481,1697,1724]" pageId="3">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Local endemic species of Sierra de Nipe. It is only known from the Charrascales de La Caridad, near the Naranjo river (
<geoCoordinate id="BC8950326B54BB77FDB9C4B303FAF917" box="[537,688,1733,1760]" degrees="20.474592" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" precision="1" value="20.474592">20.474592 N</geoCoordinate>
; - 
<geoCoordinate id="BC8950326B54BB77FD64C4B3022BF917" box="[708,865,1733,1760]" degrees="75.740322" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" precision="1" value="-75.74032">75.740322 W</geoCoordinate>
), Mayarí municipality, 
<collectingRegion id="1B79F8176B54BB77FBC7C4B00466F917" box="[1127,1324,1734,1760]" country="Cuba" name="Holguin" pageId="3">Holguín province</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="41862A706B54BB77FA9BC4B004D7F917" box="[1339,1437,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1449,1471]" captionTargetBox="[177,1415,405,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-108@3.[151,1436,389,1424]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical location of the Myrcia urquiolae population in Holguín (eastern Cuba), La Mensura-Piloto National Park, near the Naranjo river, in the charrascales of La Caridad." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605256" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605256/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). It grows in xeromorphic sub-thorny thickets over serpentinite rocks, on ferromagnesian red-brownish fersialitic soils, between 
<quantity id="1E459B106B54BB77FF4DC57B0027F8DF" box="[237,365,1805,1832]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" unit="m" value="375.0" valueMax="450.0" valueMin="300.0">300–450 m</quantity>
elev. The shrub strata of the charrascal, where the species lives, varies between 
<quantity id="1E459B106B54BB77FB58C578040AF8DF" box="[1272,1344,1806,1832]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 m</quantity>
in height and its cover on the ground is 70–80%. Species composition include 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FC06C5440044F887" authority="(Standley 1918: 42) Delprete (1999: 221)" authorityName="Delprete" authorityPageNumber="221" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Standley" baseAuthorityPageNumber="42" baseAuthorityYear="1918" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Mazaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="shaferi">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FC06C544051CF8BB" box="[934,1110,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3">Mazaea shaferi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FBC6C5440473F8BB" author="Standley, P. C." box="[1126,1337,1842,1868]" pageId="3" pagination="3 - 86" refId="ref3168" refString="Standley, P. C. (1918) Rubiaceae. North American Flora 32 (1): 3 - 86." type="journal article" year="1918">Standley 1918: 42</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FAEBC5440044F887" author="Delprete, P. G." pageId="3" pagination="217 - 230" refId="ref2438" refString="Delprete, P. G. (1999) The Cuban endemic genera Ariadne, Mazaea, Acunaeanthus, Phyllomelia (Rondeletieae), and Eosanthe (Rubiaceae). Brittonia 51 (2): 217 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2666631" type="journal article" year="1999">Delprete (1999: 221)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FEBBC5200285F887" authority="(Grisebach 1866: 67) Engler (1883: 367)" authorityName="Engler" authorityPageNumber="367" authorityYear="1883" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="67" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[283,975,1877,1904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Metopium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosum">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FEBBC52000BCF898" box="[283,502,1878,1903]" italics="true" pageId="3">Metopium venosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FDA6C52003ACF887" author="Grisebach, A." box="[518,742,1877,1904]" pageId="3" refId="ref2767" refString="Grisebach, A. (1866) Catalogus plantarum cubensium exhibens collectionem Wrightianam aliasque minores ex insula Cuba missas. Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 177" type="book" year="1866">Grisebach 1866: 67</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FD56C5200285F887" author="Engler, A." box="[758,975,1877,1904]" pageId="3" pagination="171 - 546" refId="ref2488" refString="Engler, A. (1883) Anacardiaceae. Monographiae Phanerogamarum 4: 171 - 546." type="journal article" year="1883">Engler (1883: 367)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FC7BC52000FAF863" authority="(Grisebach 1866: 93) M. Gomez (1894: 68)" authorityName="M. Gomez" authorityPageNumber="68" authorityYear="1894" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="93" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rosmarinifolia">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FC7BC52005ABF887" box="[987,1249,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="3">Miconia rosmarinifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FB50C52001EFF863" author="Grisebach, A." pageId="3" refId="ref2767" refString="Grisebach, A. (1866) Catalogus plantarum cubensium exhibens collectionem Wrightianam aliasque minores ex insula Cuba missas. Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 177" type="book" year="1866">Grisebach 1866: 93</bibRefCitation>
) M. 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FF7EC50C00FAF863" author="Gomez, M." box="[222,432,1913,1940]" pageId="3" pagination="41 - 71" refId="ref2594" refString="Gomez, M. (1894) Catalogo de las periantiadas cubanas, espontaneas y cultivadas. Anales de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural 23: 41 - 71." type="journal article" year="1894">Gómez (1894: 68)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FE1DC50C0292F863" authority="Grisebach (1866: 136)" authorityName="Grisebach" authorityPageNumber="136" authorityYear="1866" box="[445,984,1913,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rufovaginata">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FE1DC50C0385F863" box="[445,719,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3">Psychotria rufovaginata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FD77C50C0292F863" author="Grisebach, A." box="[727,984,1913,1940]" pageId="3" refId="ref2767" refString="Grisebach, A. (1866) Catalogus plantarum cubensium exhibens collectionem Wrightianam aliasque minores ex insula Cuba missas. Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 177" type="book" year="1866">Grisebach (1866: 136)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FC45C50C04DFF863" authority="Britton (1915: 505)" authorityName="Britton" authorityPageNumber="505" authorityYear="1915" box="[997,1429,1913,1940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Plumeria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nipensis">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FC45C50C05FBF864" box="[997,1201,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3">Plumeria nipensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FB19C50C04DFF863" author="Britton, N. L." box="[1209,1429,1913,1940]" pageId="3" pagination="487 - 517" refId="ref2199" refString="Britton, N. L. (1915) Studies of West Indian plants - VII. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 42: 487 - 517. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2479726" type="journal article" year="1915">Britton (1915: 505)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
y 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FF28C5E80226F84F" authority="(Grisebach 1866: 125) Borhidi (2002: 227)" authorityName="Borhidi" authorityPageNumber="227" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Grisebach" baseAuthorityPageNumber="125" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[136,876,1949,1976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Solenandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtifolia">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FF28C5E80034F84F" box="[136,382,1950,1976]" italics="true" pageId="3">Solenandra myrtifolia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FE2DC5E80333F84F" author="Grisebach, A." box="[397,633,1949,1976]" pageId="3" refId="ref2767" refString="Grisebach, A. (1866) Catalogus plantarum cubensium exhibens collectionem Wrightianam aliasque minores ex insula Cuba missas. Leipzig. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 177" type="book" year="1866">Grisebach 1866: 125</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FD29C5E80226F84F" author="Borhidi, A." box="[649,876,1950,1976]" pageId="3" pagination="223 - 231" refId="ref2166" refString="Borhidi, A. (2002) Revalidacion del genero Solenandra Hook. f. (Rubiaceae). Acta Botanica Hungarica 44 (3 - 4): 223 - 231." type="journal article" year="2002">Borhidi (2002: 227)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D90236F56B54BB77FF1DC5B70324F7D3" blockId="3.[136,1452,1554,2084]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FF1DC5B7008DF82C" bold="true" box="[189,455,1985,2011]" pageId="3">Reproductive biology</emphasis>
:—Tiny yellowish-white flowers with numerous stamens indicate probable insect pollination. Although the fruits of the new species are unknown, dispersal by birds has been reported for other 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B54BB77FAFCC5900193F7D3" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B54BB77FAFCC59004E6F808" box="[1372,1452,2022,2047]" italics="true" pageId="3">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B54BB77FF47CA7C0328F7D3" author="Torezan-Silingardi, H. M. &amp; Alves, P. E. A. M." box="[231,610,2058,2084]" pageId="3" pagination="23 - 43" refId="ref3254" refString="Torezan-Silingardi, H. M. &amp; Alves, P. E. A. M. (2004) Phenology and reproductive ecology of Myrcia rostrata and M. tomentosa (Myrtaceae) in Central Brazil. Phyton 44 (1): 23 - 43." type="journal article" year="2004">Torezan-Silingardi &amp; Alves 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="91A7657E6B53BB70FF1DC2E80035FD0F" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D90236F56B53BB70FF1DC2E803E0FE66" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,760]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FF1DC2E800E1FF4F" bold="true" box="[189,427,158,184]" pageId="4">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FE6FC2E903D9FF4F" authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[463,659,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FE6FC2E903D9FF4F" box="[463,659,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from only one locality, which was affected by fire in 
<date id="AD0310356B53BB70FAC2C2E8018EFF2B" pageId="4" value="2019-03">March 2019</date>
. In the only population known to date, 
<specimenCount id="CFBBFD7C6B53BB70FDC9C2B40388FF2B" box="[617,706,194,221]" pageId="4" type="adult">25 adult</specimenCount>
individuals have been registered in an extent of occurrence and area of occupation of 
<quantity id="1E459B106B53BB70FEE4C2900036FEF7" box="[324,380,230,256]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
<superScript id="2EC89BBD6B53BB70FEDCC29000CEFF03" attach="left" box="[380,388,230,244]" fontSize="6" pageId="4">2</superScript>
. Although this locality is located within La Mensura-Piloto National Park, a managed protected area of national significance, this site is vulnerable to increased fire frequency. For this reason, a future decrease in the area, extent and quality of habitat and in the number of mature individuals is projected. Therefore, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B53BB70FF28C3240054FE9B" author="IUCN" box="[136,286,338,364]" pageId="4" refId="ref2803" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 22 December 2021)." type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the available data support the evaluation of 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FCC7C3250563FE9B" authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[871,1065,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FCC7C3250563FE9B" box="[871,1065,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as Critically Endangered (CR), by criteria: B1ab(ii, iii,v)+2ab(ii, iii,v); C2a(i,ii); D.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D90236F56B53BB70FF1DC3EC0035FD0F" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,760]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FF1DC3EC00E6FE43" bold="true" box="[189,428,410,436]" pageId="4">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FE70C3ED03D9FE43" authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[464,659,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FE70C3ED03D9FE43" box="[464,659,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FCB4C3ED02BEFE43" authority="sect. Myrcia" box="[788,1012,411,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Myrcia">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FCB4C3ED022EFE43" box="[788,868,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FC04C3ED02BEFE43" box="[932,1012,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its hairy floral disc and the nonprolonged hypanthium on the summit of the ovary, characters that distinguish it from the other sections of the genus. Additionally, it presents a thickened staminal ring, which comprises more than 50% of the disc (vs. less than 30% in 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FF07C07100FEFDD7" box="[167,436,518,545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Gomidesia">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FF07C07101BDFDD7" box="[167,247,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FE9BC07000FEFDD7" box="[315,436,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">Gomidesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(O. 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B53BB70FE4BC0710328FDD6" author="Berg, O." box="[491,610,518,545]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref2146" refString="Berg, O. (1855 - 1856) Revisio Myrtacearum Americae. Linnaea 27: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1855">Berg 1855</bibRefCitation>
–1856: 5) B. S. Amorim &amp; E. Lucas in 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B53BB70FB8BC0710458FDD7" author="Lucas, E. J. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Lima, D. F. &amp; Lourenco, A. R. L. &amp; NicLughadha, E. M. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Rosa, P. O. &amp; Rosario, A. S. &amp; Santos, L. L. &amp; Santos, M. F. &amp; Souza, M. C. &amp; Staggemeier, V. G. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M." box="[1067,1298,518,545]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref3022" refString="Lucas, E. J., Amorim, B. S., Lima, D. F., Lourenco, A. R. L., NicLughadha, E. M., Proenca, C. E. B., Rosa, P. O., Rosario, A. S., Santos, L. L., Santos, M. F., Souza, M. C., Staggemeier, V. G., Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M. (2018) A new infra-generic classification of the species-rich Neotropical genus Myrcia s. l. Kew Bulletin 73 (9): 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / S 12225 - 017 - 9730 - 5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Lucas 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FBD6C07105FBFDD7" box="[1142,1201,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al.</emphasis>
2018: 9
</bibRefCitation>
), and anthers with thecae of equal size that open completely in two equal parts (vs. vertically displaced that retain curvature at dehiscence) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B53BB70FEE8C0390344FD9F" author="Lucas, E. J. &amp; Amorim, B. S. &amp; Lima, D. F. &amp; Lourenco, A. R. L. &amp; NicLughadha, E. M. &amp; Proenca, C. E. B. &amp; Rosa, P. O. &amp; Rosario, A. S. &amp; Santos, L. L. &amp; Santos, M. F. &amp; Souza, M. C. &amp; Staggemeier, V. G. &amp; Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M." box="[328,526,590,617]" pageId="4" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref3022" refString="Lucas, E. J., Amorim, B. S., Lima, D. F., Lourenco, A. R. L., NicLughadha, E. M., Proenca, C. E. B., Rosa, P. O., Rosario, A. S., Santos, L. L., Santos, M. F., Souza, M. C., Staggemeier, V. G., Vasconcelos, T. N. C. &amp; Sobral, M. (2018) A new infra-generic classification of the species-rich Neotropical genus Myrcia s. l. Kew Bulletin 73 (9): 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / S 12225 - 017 - 9730 - 5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Lucas 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FE32C0390089FD9F" box="[402,451,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FCCAC03902B6FD9F" authorityName="Z. Acosta" authorityYear="2022" box="[874,1020,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urquiolae">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FCCAC03902B6FD9F" box="[874,1020,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">M. urquiolae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FB80C039044BFD9F" authority="sect. Myrcia" box="[1056,1281,591,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Myrcia">
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FB80C039053AFD9F" box="[1056,1136,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FB11C039044BFD9F" box="[1201,1281,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="4">Myrcia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proven by 
<bibRefCitation id="BD2C4B046B53BB70FF28C00400CCFD7B" author="Flickinger, J. A. &amp; Jestrow, B. &amp; Oviedo, R. &amp; Santiago-Valentin, E. &amp; Sustache-Sustache, J. &amp; Jimenez-Rodriguez, F. &amp; Campbell, K. C. St. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J." box="[136,390,626,653]" pageId="4" pagination="448 - 480" refId="ref2505" refString="Flickinger, J. A., Jestrow, B., Oviedo, R., Santiago-Valentin, E., Sustache-Sustache, J., Jimenez-Rodriguez, F., Campbell, K. C. St. E. &amp; Francisco-Ortega, J. (2020) A phylogenetic survey of Myrtaceae in the Greater Antilles with nomenclatural changes for some endemic species. Taxon 69 (3): 448 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12263" type="journal article" year="2020">
Flickinger 
<emphasis id="EBC9EAE76B53BB70FEA2C005007EFD7B" box="[258,308,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="4">et al</emphasis>
. (2020
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD4D766B53BB70FE10C0050376FD7B" box="[432,572,626,653]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
